{
  "$comment": "AFL Fantasy per-season tier (Premier League / D-League) membership and champions — the single source of truth for the all-play side competition. MFL does NOT store tier membership (its all-play export returns one 24-team list with no tier markers), so it lives here. Keyed by year. `membership` maps franchiseId -> tier as teams competed THAT season; `champions` records the #1 of each tier (slugs premier-league / dleague-champion). Membership for the latest completed season is seeded from afl.config.json; future-year membership and computed champions are written by scripts/compute-afl-tier-movement.mjs (promotion/relegation roll-forward, idempotent). 2020-2024 membership was recovered from the league skin's per-year grouping scripts (mfl.football/afl-fantasy.com/assets/js/premierleague-YYYY.js) which hardcode each season's Premier/D-League rosters; those years' champions remain hand-entered. The competition began in 2016 as ONE combined 24-team all-play table (no separate tier champions that year); its top 12 formed the 2017 Premier League, the bottom 12 the D-League. Split-tier seasons ran 2017+ (champions in awards-history.json, source manual:league-awards), but per-season ROSTERS for 2017-2019 were never recorded anywhere recoverable (no grouping script is published before 2020), so those seasons have no membership here and render as a combined table. Movement rule: owners who JOIN the league always start in the D-League regardless of which tier their franchise slot held — a turnover year relegates correspondingly fewer Premier League teams, so the pure constitution roll-forward cannot reconstruct those years.",
